37 // Supported shift-links (client generated and server side)
38 // |color|Hachievement:achievement_id:player_guid_hex:completed_0_1:mm:dd:yy_from_2000:criteriaMask1:criteriaMask2:criteriaMask3:criteriaMask4|h[name]|h|r
39 // - client, item icon shift click, not used in server currently
40 // |color|Hachievement_criteria:criteria_id|h[name]|h|r
41 // |color|Harea:area_id|h[name]|h|r
42 // |color|Hareatrigger:id|h[name]|h|r
43 // |color|Hareatrigger_target:id|h[name]|h|r
44 // |color|Hcreature:creature_guid|h[name]|h|r
45 // |color|Hcreature_entry:creature_id|h[name]|h|r
46 // |color|Henchant:recipe_spell_id|h[prof_name: recipe_name]|h|r - client, at shift click in recipes list dialog
47 // |color|Hgameevent:id|h[name]|h|r
48 // |color|Hgameobject:go_guid|h[name]|h|r
49 // |color|Hgameobject_entry:go_id|h[name]|h|r
50 // |color|Hglyph:glyph_slot_id:glyph_prop_id|h[%s]|h|r - client, at shift click in glyphs dialog, GlyphSlot.dbc, GlyphProperties.dbc
51 // |color|Hitem:item_id:perm_ench_id:gem1:gem2:gem3:0:0:0:0:reporter_level|h[name]|h|r
52 // - client, item icon shift click
53 // |color|Hitemset:itemset_id|h[name]|h|r
54 // |color|Hplayer:name|h[name]|h|r - client, in some messages, at click copy only name instead link, so no way generate it in client string send to server
55 // |color|Hpool:pool_id|h[name]|h|r
56 // |color|Hquest:quest_id:quest_level|h[name]|h|r - client, quest list name shift-click
57 // |color|Hskill:skill_id|h[name]|h|r
58 // |color|Hspell:spell_id|h[name]|h|r - client, spellbook spell icon shift-click
59 // |color|Htalent:talent_id,rank|h[name]|h|r - client, talent icon shift-click rank==-1 if shift-copy unlearned talent
60 // |color|Htaxinode:id|h[name]|h|r
61 // |color|Htele:id|h[name]|h|r
62 // |color|Htitle:id|h[name]|h|r
63 // |color|Htrade:spell_id:cur_value:max_value:unk3int:unk3str|h[name]|h|r - client, spellbook profession icon shift-click

1191 bool ChatHandler::hasStringAbbr(const char* name, const char* part) const
1192 {

1195  {

1198  return false;
1199 
1200  for (;;)
1201  {
1202  if (!*part)
1203  return true;
1204  if (!*name)
1205  return false;
1206  if (tolower(*name) != tolower(*part))
1207  return false;
1208  ++name; ++part;

1212 
1213  return true;

1278 void ChatHandler::CheckIntegrity(ChatCommand* table, ChatCommand* parentCommand) const
1279 {
1280  for (uint32 i = 0; table[i].Name != nullptr; ++i)
1281  {
1282  ChatCommand* command = &table[i];
1283 
1284  if (parentCommand && command->SecurityLevel < parentCommand->SecurityLevel)
1285  sLog.outError("Subcommand '%s' of command '%s' have less access level (%u) that parent (%u)",
1286  command->Name, parentCommand->Name, command->SecurityLevel, parentCommand->SecurityLevel);
1287 
1288  if (!parentCommand && command->Name[0] == '\0')
1289  sLog.outError("Subcommand '' at top level");
1290 
1291  if (command->ChildCommands)
1292  {
1293  if (command->Handler)
1294  {
1295  if (parentCommand)
1296  sLog.outError("Subcommand '%s' of command '%s' have handler and subcommands in same time, must be used '' subcommand for handler instead.",
1297  command->Name, parentCommand->Name);
1298  else
1299  sLog.outError("First level command '%s' have handler and subcommands in same time, must be used '' subcommand for handler instead.",
1300  command->Name);
1301  }
1302 
1303  if (parentCommand && command->Name[0] == '\0')
1304  sLog.outError("Subcommand '' of command '%s' have subcommands", parentCommand->Name);
1305 
1306  CheckIntegrity(command->ChildCommands, command);
1307  }
1308  else if (!command->Handler)
1309  {
1310  if (parentCommand)
1311  sLog.outError("Subcommand '%s' of command '%s' not have handler and subcommands in same time. Must have some from its!",
1312  command->Name, parentCommand->Name);
1313  else
1314  sLog.outError("First level command '%s' not have handler and subcommands in same time. Must have some from its!",
1315  command->Name);
1316  }
1317  }
1318 }

1365 ChatCommandSearchResult ChatHandler::FindCommand(ChatCommand* table, char const*& text, ChatCommand*& command, ChatCommand** parentCommand /*= nullptr*/, std::string* cmdNamePtr /*= nullptr*/, bool allAvailable /*= false*/, bool exactlyName /*= false*/) const
1366 {
1367  std::string cmd;
1368 
1369  // skip whitespaces
1370  while (*text != ' ' && *text != '\0')
1371  {
1372  cmd += *text;
1373  ++text;
1374  }
1375 
1376  while (*text == ' ') ++text;
1377 
1378  // search first level command in table
1379  for (uint32 i = 0; table[i].Name != nullptr; ++i)
1380  {
1381  if (exactlyName)
1382  {
1383  size_t len = strlen(table[i].Name);
1384  if (strncmp(table[i].Name, cmd.c_str(), len + 1) != 0)
1385  continue;
1386  }
1387  else
1388  {
1389  if (!hasStringAbbr(table[i].Name, cmd.c_str()))
1390  continue;
1391  }
1392  // select subcommand from child commands list
1393  if (table[i].ChildCommands != nullptr)
1394  {
1395  char const* oldchildtext = text;
1396  ChatCommand* parentSubcommand = nullptr;
1397  ChatCommandSearchResult res = FindCommand(table[i].ChildCommands, text, command, &parentSubcommand, cmdNamePtr, allAvailable, exactlyName);
1398 
1399  switch (res)
1400  {
1401  case CHAT_COMMAND_OK:
1402  {
1403  // if subcommand success search not return parent command, then this parent command is owner of child commands
1404  if (parentCommand)
1405  *parentCommand = parentSubcommand ? parentSubcommand : &table[i];
1406 
1407  // Name == "" is special case: restore original command text for next level "" (where parentSubcommand==nullptr)
1408  if (command->Name[0] == '\0' && !parentSubcommand)
1409  text = oldchildtext;
1410 
1411  return CHAT_COMMAND_OK;
1412  }
1413  case CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN:
1414  {
1415  // command not found directly in child command list, return child command list owner
1416  command = &table[i];
1417  if (parentCommand)
1418  *parentCommand = nullptr; // we don't known parent of table list at this point
1419 
1420  text = oldchildtext; // restore text to stated just after parse found parent command
1421  return CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN_SUBCOMMAND; // we not found subcommand for table[i]
1422  }
1423  case CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN_SUBCOMMAND:
1424  default:
1425  {
1426  // some deep subcommand not found, if this second level subcommand then parentCommand can be nullptr, use known value for it
1427  if (parentCommand)
1428  *parentCommand = parentSubcommand ? parentSubcommand : &table[i];
1429  return res;
1430  }
1431  }
1432  }
1433 
1434  // must be available (not checked for subcommands case because parent command expected have most low access that all subcommands always
1435  if (!allAvailable && !isAvailable(table[i]))
1436  continue;
1437 
1438  // must be have handler is explicitly selected
1439  if (!table[i].Handler)
1440  continue;
1441 
1442  // command found directly in to table
1443  command = &table[i];
1444 
1445  // unknown table owner at this point
1446  if (parentCommand)
1447  *parentCommand = nullptr;
1448 
1449  if (cmdNamePtr)
1450  *cmdNamePtr = cmd;
1451 
1452  return CHAT_COMMAND_OK;
1453  }
1454 
1455  // command not found in table directly
1456  command = nullptr;
1457 
1458  // unknown table owner at this point
1459  if (parentCommand)
1460  *parentCommand = nullptr;
1461 
1462  if (cmdNamePtr)
1463  *cmdNamePtr = cmd;
1464 
1465  return CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN;
1466 }

1475 void ChatHandler::ExecuteCommand(const char* text)
1476 {
1477  std::string fullcmd = text; // original `text` can't be used. It content destroyed in command code processing.
1478 
1479  ChatCommand* command = nullptr;
1480  ChatCommand* parentCommand = nullptr;
1481 
1482  ChatCommandSearchResult res = FindCommand(getCommandTable(), text, command, &parentCommand);
1483 
1484  switch (res)
1485  {
1486  case CHAT_COMMAND_OK:
1487  {
1488  SetSentErrorMessage(false);
1489  if ((this->*(command->Handler))((char*)text)) // text content destroyed at call
1490  {
1491  if (command->SecurityLevel > SEC_PLAYER)
1492  LogCommand(fullcmd.c_str());
1493  }
1494  // some commands have custom error messages. Don't send the default one in these cases.
1495  else if (!HasSentErrorMessage())
1496  {
1497  if (!command->Help.empty())
1498  SendSysMessage(command->Help.c_str());
1499  else
1500  SendSysMessage(LANG_CMD_SYNTAX);
1501 
1502  if (ChatCommand* showCommand = (command->Name[0] == '\0' && parentCommand ? parentCommand : command))
1503  if (ChatCommand* childs = showCommand->ChildCommands)
1504  ShowHelpForSubCommands(childs, showCommand->Name);
1505 
1506  SetSentErrorMessage(true);
1507  }
1508  break;
1509  }
1510  case CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN_SUBCOMMAND:
1511  {
1512  SendSysMessage(LANG_NO_SUBCMD);
1513  ShowHelpForCommand(command->ChildCommands, text);
1514  SetSentErrorMessage(true);
1515  break;
1516  }
1517  case CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN:
1518  {
1519  SendSysMessage(LANG_NO_CMD);
1520  SetSentErrorMessage(true);
1521  break;
1522  }
1523  }
1524 }

1538 bool ChatHandler::SetDataForCommandInTable(ChatCommand* commandTable, const char* text, uint32 security, std::string const& help)
1539 {
1540  std::string fullcommand = text; // original `text` can't be used. It content destroyed in command code processing.
1541 
1542  ChatCommand* command = nullptr;
1543  std::string cmdName;
1544 
1545  ChatCommandSearchResult res = FindCommand(commandTable, text, command, nullptr, &cmdName, true, true);
1546 
1547  switch (res)
1548  {
1549  case CHAT_COMMAND_OK:
1550  {
1551  if (command->SecurityLevel != security)
1552  DETAIL_LOG("Table `command` overwrite for command '%s' default security (%u) by %u",
1553  fullcommand.c_str(), command->SecurityLevel, security);
1554 
1555  command->SecurityLevel = security;
1556  command->Help = help;
1557  return true;
1558  }
1559  case CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN_SUBCOMMAND:
1560  {
1561  // command have subcommands, but not '' subcommand and then any data in `command` useless for it.
1562  if (cmdName.empty())
1563  sLog.outErrorDb("Table `command` have command '%s' that only used with some subcommand selection, it can't have help or overwritten access level, skip.", cmdName.c_str());
1564  else
1565  sLog.outErrorDb("Table `command` have unexpected subcommand '%s' in command '%s', skip.", cmdName.c_str(), fullcommand.c_str());
1566  return false;
1567  }
1568  case CHAT_COMMAND_UNKNOWN:
1569  {
1570  sLog.outErrorDb("Table `command` have nonexistent command '%s', skip.", cmdName.c_str());
1571  return false;
1572  }
1573  }
1574 
1575  return false;
1576 }

1698 {

1720 bool ChatHandler::CheckEscapeSequences(const char* message)
1721 {
1722  /*
1723 
1724  valid examples:
1725  |cffa335ee|Hitem:812:0:0:0:0:0:0:0:70|h[Glowing Brightwood Staff]|h|r
1726  |cff808080|Hquest:2278:47|h[The Platinum Discs]|h|r
1727  |cffffd000|Htrade:4037:1:150:1:6AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAOAADAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAIAAAAAAAAA|h[Engineering]|h|r
1728  |cff4e96f7|Htalent:2232:-1|h[Taste for Blood]|h|r
1729  |cff71d5ff|Hspell:21563|h[Command]|h|r
1730  |cffffd000|Henchant:3919|h[Engineering: Rough Dynamite]|h|r
1731  |cffffff00|Hachievement:546:0000000000000001:0:0:0:-1:0:0:0:0|h[Safe Deposit]|h|r
1732  |cff66bbff|Hglyph:21:762|h[Glyph of Bladestorm]|h|r
1733 
1734  | will be escaped to ||
1735  */
1736 
1737  const char validSequence[6] = "cHhhr";
1738  const char* validSequenceIterator = validSequence;
1739 
1740  // more simple checks
1741  if (sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CHAT_STRICT_LINK_CHECKING_SEVERITY) < 3)
1742  {
1743  const std::string validCommands = "cHhr|";
1744 
1745  while (*message)
1746  {
1747  // find next pipe command
1748  message = strchr(message, '|');
1749 
1750  if (!message)
1751  return true;
1752 
1753  ++message;
1754  char commandChar = *message;
1755  if (validCommands.find(commandChar) == std::string::npos)
1756  return false;
1757 
1758  ++message;
1759  // validate sequence
1760  if (sWorld.getConfig(CONFIG_UINT32_CHAT_STRICT_LINK_CHECKING_SEVERITY) == 2)
1761  {
1762  if (commandChar == *validSequenceIterator)
1763  {
1764  if (validSequenceIterator == validSequence + 4)
1765  validSequenceIterator = validSequence;
1766  else
1767  ++validSequenceIterator;
1768  }
1769  else if (commandChar != '|')
1770  return false;
1771  }
1772  }
1773  return true;
1774  }
1775 
1776  std::istringstream reader(message);
1777  char buffer[256];
1778

1780

1782  Quest const* linkedQuest = nullptr;
1783  SpellEntry const* linkedSpell = nullptr;
1784  AchievementEntry const* linkedAchievement = nullptr;
1785  ItemRandomPropertiesEntry const* itemProperty = nullptr;
1786  ItemRandomSuffixEntry const* itemSuffix = nullptr;

1789  {
1790  if (validSequence == validSequenceIterator)
1791  {
1792  linkedItem = nullptr;
1793  linkedQuest = nullptr;
1794  linkedSpell = nullptr;
1795  linkedAchievement = nullptr;
1796  itemProperty = nullptr;
1797  itemSuffix = nullptr;
1798

1800  }

1802  {
1803  DEBUG_LOG("ChatHandler::isValidChatMessage sequence aborted unexpectedly");
1804  return false;
1805  }
1806 
1807  // pipe has always to be followed by at least one char
1808  if (reader.peek() == '\0')
1809  {
1810  DEBUG_LOG("ChatHandler::isValidChatMessage pipe followed by \\0");
1811  return false;
1812  }
1813 
1814  // no further pipe commands
1815  if (reader.eof())
1816  break;
1817 
1818  char commandChar;
1819  reader >> std::noskipws >> commandChar;
1820 
1821  // | in normal messages is escaped by ||
1822  if (commandChar != '|')
1823  {
1824  if (commandChar == *validSequenceIterator)
1825  {
1826  if (validSequenceIterator == validSequence + 4)
1827  validSequenceIterator = validSequence;
1828  else
1829  ++validSequenceIterator;
1830  }
1831  else
1832  {
1833  DEBUG_LOG("ChatHandler::isValidChatMessage invalid sequence, expected %c but got %c", *validSequenceIterator, commandChar);
1834  return false;
1835  }
1836  }

1838  {
1839  // no escaped pipes in sequences
1840  DEBUG_LOG("ChatHandler::isValidChatMessage got escaped pipe in sequence");
1841  return false;
1842  }
1843

1845  {
1846  case 'c':

1848  // validate color, expect 8 hex chars
1849  for (int i = 0; i < 8; ++i)
1850  {

1856  return false;
1857  }

1860  // check for hex char
1861  if (c >= '0' && c <= '9')
1862  {
1863  color |= c - '0';
1864  continue;
1865  }
1866  if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f')
1867  {
1868  color |= 10 + c - 'a';
1869  continue;

1873  }

2524 char* ChatHandler::ExtractLiteralArg(char** args, char const* lit /*= nullptr*/)
2525 {
2526  if (!*args || !** args)
2527  return nullptr;
2528 
2529  char* head = *args;
2530 
2531  // reject quoted string or link (|-started text)
2532  switch (head[0])
2533  {
2534  // reject quoted string
2535  case '[': case '\'': case '"':
2536  return nullptr;
2537  // reject link (|-started text)
2538  case '|':
2539  // client replace all | by || in raw text
2540  if (head[1] != '|')
2541  return nullptr;
2542  ++head; // skip one |
2543  break;
2544  default: break;
2545  }
2546 
2547  if (lit)
2548  {
2549  int l = strlen(lit);
2550 
2551  int largs = 0;
2552  while (head[largs] && !isWhiteSpace(head[largs]))
2553  ++largs;
2554 
2555  if (largs < l)
2556  l = largs;
2557 
2558  int diff = strncmp(head, lit, l);
2559 
2560  if (diff != 0)
2561  return nullptr;
2562 
2563  if (head[l] && !isWhiteSpace(head[l]))
2564  return nullptr;
2565 
2566  char* arg = head;
2567 
2568  if (head[l])
2569  {
2570  head[l] = '\0';
2571 
2572  head += l + 1;
2573 
2574  *args = head;
2575  }
2576  else
2577  *args = head + l;
2578 
2579  SkipWhiteSpaces(args);
2580  return arg;
2581  }
2582 
2583  char* name = strtok(head, " ");
2584 
2585  char* tail = strtok(nullptr, "");

2601 char* ChatHandler::ExtractQuotedArg(char** args, bool asis /*= false*/)
2602 {
2603  if (!*args || !** args)
2604  return nullptr;
2605 
2606  if (**args != '\'' &&** args != '"' &&** args != '[')
2607  return nullptr;
2608 
2609  char guard = (*args)[0];
2610 
2611  if (guard == '[')
2612  guard = ']';
2613

2615  char* head = asis ? *args : tail; // start arg
2616 
2617  while (*tail && *tail != guard)
2618  ++tail;
2619 
2620  if (!*tail || (tail[1] && !isWhiteSpace(tail[1]))) // fail
2621  return nullptr;
2622 
2623  if (!tail[1]) // quote is last char in string
2624  {
2625  if (!asis)
2626  *tail = '\0';
2627  }
2628  else // quote isn't last char
2629  {
2630  if (asis)
2631  ++tail;
2632 
2633  *tail = '\0';
2634  }
2635 
2636  *args = tail + 1;
2637 
2638  SkipWhiteSpaces(args);
2639 
2640  return head;

2701 char* ChatHandler::ExtractLinkArg(char** args, char const* const* linkTypes /*= nullptr*/, int* foundIdx /*= nullptr*/, char** keyPair /*= nullptr*/, char** somethingPair /*= nullptr*/)
2702 {
2703  if (!*args || !** args)
2704  return nullptr;
2705 
2706  // skip if not linked started or encoded single | (doubled by client)
2707  if ((*args)[0] != '|' || (*args)[1] == '|')
2708  return nullptr;
2709 
2710  // |color|Hlinktype:key:data...|h[name]|h|r
2711 
2712  char* head = *args;
2713 
2714  // [name] Shift-click form |color|linkType:key|h[name]|h|r
2715  // or
2716  // [name] Shift-click form |color|linkType:key:something1:...:somethingN|h[name]|h|r
2717  // or
2718  // [name] Shift-click form |linkType:key|h[name]|h|r
2719 
2720  // |color|Hlinktype:key:data...|h[name]|h|r
2721 
2722  char* tail = (*args) + 1; // skip |
2723 
2724  if (*tail != 'H') // skip color part, some links can not have color part
2725  {
2726  while (*tail && *tail != '|')
2727  ++tail;
2728 
2729  if (!*tail)
2730  return nullptr;
2731 
2732  // |Hlinktype:key:data...|h[name]|h|r
2733 
2734  ++tail; // skip |
2735  }
2736 
2737  // Hlinktype:key:data...|h[name]|h|r
2738 
2739  if (*tail != 'H')
2740  return nullptr;
2741 
2742  int linktype_idx = 0;
2743 
2744  if (linkTypes) // check link type if provided
2745  {
2746  // check linktypes (its include H in name)
2747  for (; linkTypes[linktype_idx]; ++linktype_idx)
2748  {
2749  // exactly string with follow : or |
2750  int l = strlen(linkTypes[linktype_idx]);
2751  if (strncmp(tail, linkTypes[linktype_idx], l) == 0 &&
2752  (tail[l] == ':' || tail[l] == '|'))
2753  break;
2754  }
2755 
2756  // is search fail?
2757  if (!linkTypes[linktype_idx]) // nullptr terminator in last element
2758  return nullptr;
2759 
2760  tail += strlen(linkTypes[linktype_idx]); // skip linktype string
2761 
2762  // :key:data...|h[name]|h|r
2763 
2764  if (*tail != ':')
2765  return nullptr;
2766  }
2767  else
2768  {
2769  while (*tail && *tail != ':') // skip linktype string
2770  ++tail;
2771 
2772  if (!*tail)
2773  return nullptr;
2774  }
2775 
2776  ++tail;
2777 
2778  // key:data...|h[name]|h|r
2779  char* keyStart = tail; // remember key start for return
2780 
2781  while (*tail && *tail != '|' && *tail != ':')
2782  ++tail;
2783 
2784  if (!*tail)
2785  return nullptr;
2786 
2787  char* keyEnd = tail; // remember key end for truncate
2788 
2789  // |h[name]|h|r or :something...|h[name]|h|r
2790 
2791  char* somethingStart = tail + 1;
2792  char* somethingEnd = tail + 1; // will updated later if need
2793 
2794  if (*tail == ':' && somethingPair) // optional data extraction
2795  {
2796  // :something...|h[name]|h|r
2797  ++tail;
2798 
2799  // something|h[name]|h|r or something:something2...|h[name]|h|r
2800 
2801  while (*tail && *tail != '|' && *tail != ':')
2802  ++tail;
2803 
2804  if (!*tail)
2805  return nullptr;
2806 
2807  somethingEnd = tail; // remember data end for truncate
2808  }
2809 
2810  // |h[name]|h|r or :something2...|h[name]|h|r
2811 
2812  while (*tail && (*tail != '|' || *(tail + 1) != 'h')) // skip ... part if exist
2813  ++tail;
2814 
2815  if (!*tail)
2816  return nullptr;
2817 
2818  // |h[name]|h|r
2819 
2820  tail += 2; // skip |h
2821 
2822  // [name]|h|r
2823  if (!*tail || *tail != '[')
2824  return nullptr;
2825 
2826  while (*tail && (*tail != ']' || *(tail + 1) != '|')) // skip name part
2827  ++tail;
2828 
2829  tail += 2; // skip ]|
2830 
2831  // h|r
2832  if (!*tail || *tail != 'h' || *(tail + 1) != '|')
2833  return nullptr;
2834 
2835  tail += 2; // skip h|
2836 
2837  // r
2838  if (!*tail || *tail != 'r' || (*(tail + 1) && !isWhiteSpace(*(tail + 1))))
2839  return nullptr;
2840 
2841  ++tail; // skip r
2842 
2843  // success
2844 
2845  if (*tail) // truncate all link string
2846  *(tail++) = '\0';
2847 
2848  if (foundIdx)
2849  *foundIdx = linktype_idx;
2850 
2851  if (keyPair)
2852  {
2853  keyPair[0] = keyStart;
2854  keyPair[1] = keyEnd;
2855  }
2856 
2857  if (somethingPair)
2858  {
2859  somethingPair[0] = somethingStart;
2860  somethingPair[1] = somethingEnd;
2861  }
2862 
2863  *args = tail;
2864 
2865  SkipWhiteSpaces(args);
2866 
2867  return head;
2868 }

3687 // Check/ Output if a NPC or GO (by guid) is part of a pool or game event
3688 template <typename T>
3689 void ChatHandler::ShowNpcOrGoSpawnInformation(uint32 guid)
3690 {
3691  if (uint16 pool_id = sPoolMgr.IsPartOfAPool<T>(guid))
3692  {
3693  uint16 top_pool_id = sPoolMgr.IsPartOfTopPool<Pool>(pool_id);
3694  if (!top_pool_id || top_pool_id == pool_id)
3695  {
3696  PoolTemplateData const& pool_template = sPoolMgr.GetPoolTemplate(pool_id);
3697  PSendSysMessage(LANG_NPC_GO_INFO_POOL, uint32(pool_id), pool_template.description.c_str());
3698  }
3699  else
3700  {
3701  PoolTemplateData const& pool_template = sPoolMgr.GetPoolTemplate(pool_id);
3702  PoolTemplateData const& mother_template = sPoolMgr.GetPoolTemplate(top_pool_id);
3703  PSendSysMessage(LANG_NPC_GO_INFO_TOP_POOL, uint32(pool_id), pool_template.description.c_str(), uint32(top_pool_id), mother_template.description.c_str());
3704  }
3705 
3706  if (int16 event_id = sGameEventMgr.GetGameEventId<Pool>(top_pool_id))
3707  {
3708  GameEventMgr::GameEventDataMap const& events = sGameEventMgr.GetEventMap();
3709  GameEventData const& eventData = events[std::abs(event_id)];
3710 
3711  if (event_id > 0)
3712  PSendSysMessage(LANG_NPC_GO_INFO_POOL_GAME_EVENT_S, uint32(top_pool_id), uint32(std::abs(event_id)), eventData.description.c_str());
3713  else
3714  PSendSysMessage(LANG_NPC_GO_INFO_POOL_GAME_EVENT_D, uint32(top_pool_id), uint32(std::abs(event_id)), eventData.description.c_str());
3715  }
3716  }
3717  else if (int16 event_id = sGameEventMgr.GetGameEventId<T>(guid))
3718  {
3719  GameEventMgr::GameEventDataMap const& events = sGameEventMgr.GetEventMap();
3720  GameEventData const& eventData = events[std::abs(event_id)];
3721 
3722  if (event_id > 0)
3723  PSendSysMessage(LANG_NPC_GO_INFO_GAME_EVENT_S, uint32(std::abs(event_id)), eventData.description.c_str());
3724  else
3725  PSendSysMessage(LANG_NPC_GO_INFO_GAME_EVENT_D, uint32(std::abs(event_id)), eventData.description.c_str());

3781 void ChatHandler::BuildChatPacket(WorldPacket& data, ChatMsg msgtype, char const* message, Language language /*= LANG_UNIVERSAL*/, ChatTagFlags chatTag /*= CHAT_TAG_NONE*/,
3782  ObjectGuid const& senderGuid /*= ObjectGuid()*/, char const* senderName /*= nullptr*/,
3783  ObjectGuid const& targetGuid /*= ObjectGuid()*/, char const* targetName /*= nullptr*/,
3784  char const* channelName /*= nullptr*/, uint32 achievementId /*= 0*/)
3785 {
3786  const bool isGM = (chatTag & CHAT_TAG_GM) != 0;
3787  bool isAchievement = false;
3788 
3789  data.Initialize((isGM && language != LANG_ADDON) ? SMSG_GM_MESSAGECHAT : SMSG_MESSAGECHAT);
3790  data << uint8(msgtype);
3791  data << uint32(language);
3792  data << ObjectGuid(senderGuid);
3793  data << uint32(0); // 2.1.0
3794 
3795  switch (msgtype)
3796  {
3797  case CHAT_MSG_MONSTER_SAY:
3798  case CHAT_MSG_MONSTER_PARTY:
3799  case CHAT_MSG_MONSTER_YELL:
3800  case CHAT_MSG_MONSTER_WHISPER:
3801  case CHAT_MSG_MONSTER_EMOTE:
3802  case CHAT_MSG_RAID_BOSS_WHISPER:
3803  case CHAT_MSG_RAID_BOSS_EMOTE:
3804  case CHAT_MSG_BNET:
3805  case CHAT_MSG_WHISPER_FOREIGN:
3806  MANGOS_ASSERT(senderName);
3807  data << uint32(strlen(senderName) + 1);
3808  data << senderName;
3809  data << ObjectGuid(targetGuid); // Unit Target
3810  if (targetGuid && !targetGuid.IsPlayer() && !targetGuid.IsPet() && (msgtype != CHAT_MSG_WHISPER_FOREIGN))
3811  {
3812  data << uint32(strlen(targetName) + 1); // target name length
3813  data << targetName; // target name
3814  }
3815  break;
3816  case CHAT_MSG_BG_SYSTEM_NEUTRAL:
3817  case CHAT_MSG_BG_SYSTEM_ALLIANCE:
3818  case CHAT_MSG_BG_SYSTEM_HORDE:
3819  data << ObjectGuid(targetGuid); // Unit Target
3820  if (targetGuid && !targetGuid.IsPlayer())
3821  {
3822  MANGOS_ASSERT(targetName);
3823  data << uint32(strlen(targetName) + 1); // target name length
3824  data << targetName; // target name
3825  }
3826  break;
3827  case CHAT_MSG_ACHIEVEMENT:
3828  case CHAT_MSG_GUILD_ACHIEVEMENT:
3829  data << ObjectGuid(targetGuid); // Unit Target
3830  isAchievement = true;
3831  break;
3832  default:
3833  if (isGM)
3834  {
3835  MANGOS_ASSERT(senderName);
3836  data << uint32(strlen(senderName) + 1);
3837  data << senderName;
3838  }
3839 
3840  if (msgtype == CHAT_MSG_CHANNEL)
3841  {
3842  MANGOS_ASSERT(channelName);
3843  data << channelName;
3844  }
3845  data << ObjectGuid(targetGuid);
3846  break;
3847  }
3848  MANGOS_ASSERT(message);
3849  data << uint32(strlen(message) + 1);
3850  data << message;
3851  data << uint8(chatTag);
3852 
3853  if (isAchievement)
3854  data << uint32(achievementId);
3855 }
